{# Retry options shown on a failed real-mode run.

   Two POST forms (no JS): each carries a ``mode`` field and posts to
   ``/runs/{run_id}/retry``. Soft retry reuses the same root thread id
   so the failing phase resumes from its langgraph checkpoint; hard
   retry generates a fresh thread id (cached phases still skip via
   ``cache_ns``, the failing phase gets a clean conversation).

   Replace target: ``#retry-banner``. The wrapper keeps the id so
   future replaces — e.g. clearing the banner if the run somehow
   transitions back to running — would still hit the right element.

   ctx:
     run_id  — id of the failed run; submit posts to /runs/{run_id}/retry
#}
<section id="retry-banner" class="retry-banner">
  <div class="retry-banner-content">
    <p class="retry-explainer">
      <strong>This run failed.</strong> Two options for picking it up
      again — both reuse the cache, so phases that already succeeded
      will skip on the new run.
    </p>
    <div class="retry-buttons">
      <form method="post"
            action="/runs/{{ run_id }}/retry"
            class="retry-form">
        <input type="hidden" name="mode" value="soft">
        <button type="submit" class="retry-btn retry-soft"
                title="Resume from the langgraph checkpoint of the failing phase. Cheap and fast, but inherits the agent state at the moment of failure (so loop-on-bad-tool-call retries will probably loop again).">
          Soft retry
          <span class="retry-detail">— resume from checkpoint</span>
        </button>
      </form>
      <form method="post"
            action="/runs/{{ run_id }}/retry"
            class="retry-form">
        <input type="hidden" name="mode" value="hard">
        <button type="submit" class="retry-btn retry-hard"
                title="Restart the failing phase with a fresh conversation. Cached phases still skip (same cache_ns); only the failing phase re-runs from scratch. Use when soft retry isn't escaping the bad agent state.">
          Hard retry
          <span class="retry-detail">— fresh conversation</span>
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
